  "content": "corvia-cli -- workspace create --help`\nExpected: shows create flags (name, --repo, --template, --local).\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m2.1): scaffold corvia workspace CLI subcommand group\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Workspace Module — Repo Cloning and Directory Setup\n\nCreate a `workspace.rs` module in `corvia-cli` that handles the core workspace operations: directory scaffolding, repo cloning, config generation.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `crates/corvia-cli/src/workspace.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs` (add `mod workspace;`)\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-cli/Cargo.toml` (add `git2` dependency if not present)\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests for workspace directory scaffolding**\n\nCreate `crates/corvia-cli/src/workspace.rs` with test module first:\n\n```rust\nuse anyhow::Result;\nuse corvia_common::config::{CorviaConfig, WorkspaceConfig, RepoConfig};\nuse std::path::{Path, PathBuf};\n\n/// Derive a repo name from a URL (e.g., \"https://github.com/org/my-repo\" -> \"my-repo\")\npub fn repo_name_from_url(url: &str) -> String {\n    url.trim_end_matches('/')\n        .rsplit('/')\n        .next()\n        .unwrap_or(\"unknown\")\n        .trim_end_matches(\".git\")\n        .to_string()\n}\n\n/// Parse local overrides from \"name=path\" format\npub fn parse_local_overrides(locals: &[String]) -> Result<Vec<(String, String)>> {\n    locals\n        .iter()\n        .map(|s| {",
